&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Length of the train = 800m&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed of the train = 90 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Train crosses the&amp;nbsp;man in&amp;nbsp;8 seconds&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In relative motion, If two objects are coming to each other from opposite directions, then total speed becomes the sum of their speed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Speed = Distance/Time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the speed of man is x m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the concept, we have&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relative speed = (90 + x) m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, According to the formula, we have&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(90 + x) m/s&amp;nbsp; = 800/8 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = (100 - 90) m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 10 m/s&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The speed of man is 10 m/s.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A and B can complete a task in 50 days, B and C can complete it in 37.5 days while C and A can do the same task together in 30 days.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suppose Efficiencies of A, B and C are a, b and c respectively;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suppose total work = 150 units (LCM of 50, 37.5 and 30)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a + b = 150/50 = 3 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b + c = 150/37.5 = 4 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c + a = 150/30 = 5 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adding all three:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(a + b + c) = (3 + 4 + 5)/2 = 6 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c = 6 &amp;ndash; 3 = 3 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = 6 &amp;ndash; 4 = 2 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;b = 6 &amp;ndash; 5 = 1 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time in which A can complete the task alone = 150/2 = 75 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time in which A can complete the task alone = 150/1 = 150 days&lt;/p&gt;
Time in which A can complete the task alone = 150/3 = 50 days

&lt;p&gt;Given:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\Rightarrow \dfrac{0.49 x^2 + 0.09 y^2 + 0.42 xy}{0.4 x + 0.3x +0.3y}=?\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\Rightarrow \dfrac{(0.7x + 0.3y)^2}{(0.7x + 0.3y)} = ? \)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; ? = 0.7x + 0.3y&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ratio of efficiency of A to B = 2&amp;nbsp;∶&amp;nbsp;1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Together A and B can complete the work in 20 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Concept used:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the ratio of the efficiency of two persons is a&amp;nbsp;∶&amp;nbsp;b, then the ratio of the time in which they complete the work will be b&amp;nbsp;∶ a.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a person does the work in x days then work done by the person in 1 day = 1/x of total work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ratio of time in which they complete the work = 1&amp;nbsp;∶&amp;nbsp;2 (By using concept used)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the time taken by A be x days and time taken by B be 2x days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work completed by A in 1 day = 1/x&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work completed by B in 1 day = 1/2x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total work completed by A and B is 1 day = 1/20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 1/x + 1/2x = 1/20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 3/2x = 1/20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 30&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B can complete the work in 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 30 = 60 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; B can complete the work in 60 days&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;46px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/images/production/quesImages/quesImage37.png&quot; width=&quot;240px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Efficiency of A = 2 units and efficiency of B = 1 unit&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total efficiency of A and B = 2 + 1 = 3 units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total work = 3&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 20 = 60 units (As together they can complete the work in 20 days)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Work done by B = 60/1 = 60 days&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;there4; B can complete the work in 60 days&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time ratio of P and Q to complete the same work is = 8 : 16 = 1 : 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As we know,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Efficiency in inversely proportional to time, then&lt;/p&gt;
&amp;there4; Efficiency ratio of P and Q = 2 : 1

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pipe X is 5 times efficient than pipe Z.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the time taken by pipe X is a minutes,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And time taken by pipe Z is 5a minutes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tank filled in 1 minute = (1/10)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tank filled by pipe X in 1 minute = (1/a)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tank filled by pipe Z in 1 minute = (1/5a)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to question&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(1/a) + (1/5a) = (1/10)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (5a + a)/(a)(5a) = (1/10)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 6a/5a&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;= (1/10)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; (6 &amp;times; 10)/5 = a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 12 = a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time taken by pipe X is 12 minutes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Time taken by pipe Z is 60 minutes [i.e. 12 &amp;times; 5]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The efficiency of L is 3 times that of M&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Both working together can complete the work in 12 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula Used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total Work = Efficiency&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; Time&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the efficiency of M be &amp;#39;x&amp;#39; units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Efficiency of L = 3x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Combined efficiency = x + 3x = 4x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total work = (4x) &amp;times; 12 = 48x units&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Time required by L alone to finish the task = (48x)/3x = 16 days&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; L alone will complete the work in 16 days.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Pipes P and Q can fill a tank in 12 hours and 36 hours&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P&amp;rsquo;s one-hour work = 1/12&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Q&amp;rsquo;s one-hour work = 1/36&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;P and Q&amp;lsquo;s one-hour work = 1/12 + 1/36 = 4/36 = 1/9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total time taken by both P and Q to fill the tank = 1/(1/9) = 9 hours&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
sec&amp;theta; + tan&amp;theta; = 2&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ----(1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Pythagorean theorem:&lt;br /&gt;
P&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;+ B&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;= H&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
1 + tan&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;theta; = sec&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;theta;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
sec&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;theta;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; tan&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;theta; = 1&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; (sec&amp;theta; + tan&amp;theta;)(sec&amp;theta;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; tan&amp;theta;) = 1&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (sec&amp;theta;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; tan&amp;theta;) = 1&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; sec&amp;theta;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; tan&amp;theta; = 1/2&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ----(2)&lt;br /&gt;
On adding equation (1) &amp;amp; (2)&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; sec&amp;theta; = 2&amp;nbsp;+ 1/2&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; sec&amp;theta; = 5/2&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; sec&amp;theta; = 5/4 = H/B&lt;br /&gt;
From Pythagorean theorem:&lt;br /&gt;
H = 5, B = 4 &amp;amp; P = 3&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;rArr; sin&amp;theta; = P/H = 3/5&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The value of sin&amp;theta; is 3/5.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ratio between two numbers =&amp;nbsp;4 : 5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the numbers be 4x and 5x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to the question&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(4x + 4)/(5x + 4) = 6/7&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 28x + 28 = 30x + 24&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 2x = 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Difference of numbers = 5x - 4x = x = 2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The required answer is 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;x &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x = 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(a &amp;ndash; b)&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;= a&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; b&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 3ab(a &amp;ndash; b)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our given expression is x&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 1/x = 4&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Taking cube on both the sides,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(x&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 1/x)&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt; = 4&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; x&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x&lt;sup&gt;3&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;3x&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 1/x(x &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x) = 64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;3 &amp;times; 4 = 64&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; ----(∵ x &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x = 4)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 64&amp;nbsp;+ 12&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp;1/x&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative; line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em; font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 76&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The value of the given expression is 76&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

