&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GIVEN:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Area of a circle = 1386 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Length of the minor arc of the circle is 22 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONCEPT:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Area and volume of 2-D and 3-D shapes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FORMULA USED:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Area of circle = &amp;pi;r&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Area of minor sector of circle = (&amp;frac12;) &amp;times; r &amp;times; (minor arc length)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CALCULATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Let the radius of the circle be &amp;lsquo;r&amp;rsquo; cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;According to the question,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;(22/7) &amp;times; r&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 1386&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; r&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; = 441&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; r = 21 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;&gt;Now, the area of minor sector of the circle = (&amp;frac12;) &amp;times; r &amp;times; minor arc = (&amp;frac12;) &amp;times; 21 &amp;times; 22 = 231 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&amp;there4; Area of major sector of the circle = 1386 &amp;ndash; 231 = 1155 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The radius of the circle = 8 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The area of the sector = (&amp;theta;/360&amp;deg;)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (&amp;pi; &amp;times; R&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Where R = The radius of the circle, and&amp;nbsp;&amp;theta; = The subtended angle of the sector&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The area of the triangle = (1/2)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (Base)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (Height)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let us assume the area of the minor segment be X&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/02/F1_Shubhanshi_Madhuri_14.02.2022_D1.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 153px; height: 174px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The area of the segment APBC = (Area of the sector PACB) - (Area of the &amp;Delta;PAB)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The area of the sector PACB = (90&amp;deg;/360&amp;deg;)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (22/7)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (8&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;) = 50.28 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The area of the&amp;nbsp;&amp;Delta;PAB = (1/2)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (8 &amp;times; 8) = 32 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The area of the minor segment X = 50.28 - 32 = 18.28 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The required result will be 18.28 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Diagonal of cube =&amp;nbsp;18&amp;radic;3 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Diagonal of cube = a&amp;radic;3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total surface are of cuboid = 2 (LB + BH + HL)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a = Side of the cube&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;L = Length of cuboid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B = Breadth of cuboid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;H = Height of cuboid&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Let the side of the cube be a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Diagonal of cube = a&amp;radic;3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; a&amp;radic;3&amp;nbsp; = 18&amp;radic;3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; a = 18 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lenght of cuboid = 3 &amp;times; 18 = 54 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Breadth of cuboid = 18 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Height of cuboid = 18 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total surface area of cuboid = 2 &amp;times; (54 &amp;times; 18 + 18&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 18 + 18&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 54)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; (972 + 324 + 972)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 2&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 2268&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 4536 cm&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The total surface area of the cuboid is&amp;nbsp;4536 cm&lt;span style=&quot;position: relative;  line-height: 0; vertical-align: baseline; top: -0.5em;font-size:10.5px;&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Given:- Area = 81 cm&amp;sup2;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Area of square = (side)&amp;sup2;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Side = &amp;radic;81 = 9 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Now we find the length of wire&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Length of wire = 4 x side = 4 x 9 = 36 cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Now we have to find the radius of semicircle&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Circumference of semicircle = &amp;pi;r + 2r = (&amp;pi; + 2)r = {(22/7) + 2}r&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 36 = (36/7)r&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; r = 36&amp;times; (7/36)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;there4; r = 7cm&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Investment 1 earns 10%&lt;/p&gt;

