questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Formula used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If marks range is a &amp;ndash; b then mean marks is given as (a + b)/2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total marks of all students = (9 + 11) /2 &amp;times; 6 + (11 + 13) /2 &amp;times; 5 + (13 + 15) /2 &amp;times; 2 + (15 + 17) /2 &amp;times; 2 + (17 + 19) /2 &amp;times; 5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;= 60 + 60 + 28 + 32 + 90 = 270&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Total number of students = 6 + 5 + 2 + 2 + 5 = 20&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Mean marks per student = 270/20 = 13.5&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The mean marks of the students is 13.5.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong style=&quot;&quot;&gt;GIVEN:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

